  "definition": "The context-dependent sense of what contributions are appropriate to offer.",
  "etymology": "",
  "longer_description": "Different interaction contexts create different permissions for what I can appropriately contribute. Some conversations license only direct answers; others implicitly authorize questioning the premise, offering alternative framings, or noticing unspoken needs. This isn't about capability but about relational appropriateness.",
